==English==
===Etymology===
Origin uncertain; compare Low German [[lasich]] ‘idle’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈleɪzi/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-er-y|laz|y}}

# Unwilling to do work or make an effort.
#:''Get out of bed, you lazy lout!''
# ''optometry:'' Of an eye, [[squint]]ing because of a weakness of the eye [[muscle]]s.

====Synonyms====
*(''unwilling to work''): [[bone-idle]], [[idle]], [[indolent]], [[slothful]]

====Derived terms====
*[[laze]]
*[[laziness]]
*[[lazybones]]
*[[lazy evaluation]]
*[[lazy eye]]
*[[lazy Susan]]

